			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Haste songs stacking...<a name="2218"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 4 02 12:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Many songs that have Haste components, and they can be twisted. However, the Haste component <i>won't</i> stack. I believe it's whichever is the higher haste gets used.
<br />

<br />
For example, <a target="_new" href="http://www.dotnetdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?SongID=734&amp;ForumID=23">Jonathan's Whistling Warsong</a> and <a target="_new" href="http://www.dotnetdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?SongID=701&amp;ForumID=27">Anthem De Arms</a> will stack the Strength modifier with eachother, but the higher haste (from JWW) is used. 
<br />

<br />
Other songs may cancel it out altogether. Like, <a target="_new" href="http://www.dotnetdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?SongID=740&amp;ForumID=57">Vila's Verses of Celerity</a> will overwrite, and be overwritten by Anthem de Arms.
<br />

<br />
For me information on which songs do what to which other songs, consult <a target="_new" href="http://www.dotnetdiva.com/eq/SongSpreadsheet.aspx"> Reed's Bard Song Analysis</a>.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
