			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Haste songs stacking...<a name="3418"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 22 03 12:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Quote: &quot;i should stay with the 'ole trusty Anthem De Arms and not replace it with the lvl 36 Celerity song? Now im bummed&quot;
<br />

<br />

<br />
Not sure why you said this, I think there may be a misunderstanding.
<br />

<br />
36 celerity is more haste than 10 anthem. Go with celerity.
<br />

<br />
Now, when you sing two regular haste songs (sung=spell haste), and chanter and shammy casts haste. Only the highest haste component is in effect. However, the other stat boosts do stack. If you sang anthem and celerity, the higher celerity haste would be in effect, but you would get the str boost from anthem as well.
<br />

<br />
You get 1 regular sung/spell/right clickety/proc haste (gives an icon) Lute of the Howler, Melodic Dagger, Singing Short Sword,Celerities, etc.--highest is the one in effect(also, typically, if the other buffs do not stack, some do some don't, the icon is replaced)
<br />

<br />
You get one permanent haste (Flowing black silk sash, silvery belt of contention, )--no icon--highest is the one in effect
<br />

<br />
You get one Ervai line sung haste (Icon)
<br />

<br />
You get one VahShir/Rizlona's line haste (not sure about Rizlona's and Ervaj stacking)
<br />

<br />
Ranger gets quiver haste on bow attacks and there is some special monk epic deal as well, I think
<br />

<br />
The highest haste % from each category stacks up to the haste cap--typically a cap 100% if you have items/spells that can get you there---then the cap is raised by the percentage of Vah/Rizlona's that gets applied)
<br />

<br />
I have seen it argued that Vah songs are hast cap raisers only and supply no haste of their own, my own experience seems counter to that. There is some discussion that ErVaj and Vah don't stack with each other, I am not sure. I hardly ever use ErVaj.
<br />

<br />
See:
<br />

<br />
http://cloud.prohosting.com/~talone/HasteData.htm
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
