				<td colspan="2"><span>I had experience last night that is worth sharing.  Unlike normal, I was grouping with a rogue, BST, a SK, pally and cleric, without a chanter (we have multiple chanters in guild so it's unusual I'd not be grouped with one).  I could not effectively slow the mobs so I left that to the Beastlord. In short, all they wanted from me that camp was haste, haste haste.  So at 53 this is what I played:
<br />

<br />
Celerity (the 30% one)
<br />
Ervaj (5% and yes it stacks)
<br />
Battlecry of Vah Shir (15%)
<br />

<br />
I say that Ervaj stacks for the sole reason that the icons stacked.  5% wasn't that noticible to me though the other melees liked the three songs up.  The rogue had their epic (actually was with 2 epic'd rogues at one point) and was extatic to have 91% haste (41% from epic and 50% from me).
<br />

<br />
When we moved spots and slow stuck more often, I went back to simply celerity and battlecry for the 45% haste.
<br />

<br />
My only experience with Battlecry working alone is when chanter haste fades. There does seem to be a difference with over without battlecry when that is the only haste in effect.  Can't be positive though and I'm not the type of person to go out and calculate delays and swings per second, so that's good enough for me. hehe
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian
<br />

<br />
Sure will be nice to hit 54 and get the 45% base haste song.</span></td>
